obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (11362)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for "Central Road" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11362&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1[Central Road and`
  line `Infrastructure] Fund Act, 2000.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, it shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day`
  line `of November, 2000.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (11363)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11363&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date on which the Fund is established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) "cess" means a duty in the nature of duty of excise and customs, imposed and collected on`
  line `motor spirit commonly known as petrol and high speed diesel oil for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Central ^1`
  line `[Road and Infrastructure Fund] sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) "national highways" means the highways specified in the Schedule to the National Highways`
  line `Act, 1956 (48 of 1956) or any other highway declared as national highway under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 2 of the said Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "National Highways Authority of India" means an authority constituted under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 3 of the National Highways Authority of India Act, 1988 (68 of 1988);`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line ;
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for "Road Fund" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (e) omitted by s. 206, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (11364)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Levy and collection of cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11364&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Levy and collection of cess.--(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify, there shall be levied and collected, as a cess, a duty of excise`
  line `and customs for the purposes of this Act, on every item specified in column (2) of the ^2[Schedule I], which is`
  line `produced in or imported into India and--`
  line
  line `(a) removed from a refinery or a factory or an outlet; or`
  line
  line `(b) transferred by the person, by whom such item is produced or imported, to another person,`
  line `at such rates not exceeding the rate set forth in the corresponding entry in column (3) of the Schedule, as`
  line `^3***the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the additional duty of customs and the additional duty of excise on motor spirit`
  line `commonly known as petrol and on high speed diesel oil levied under sub-section (1) of section 109 and`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 110, as the case may be, of the Finance Act, 2018 shall be deemed to be the cess`
  line `for the purposes of this Act from the date of its levy and the proceeds thereof shall be credited to the`
  line Fund.]
  line
  line `(2) Every cess leviable under sub-section (1) on any item shall be payable by the person by whom`
  line `such item is produced, and in the case of imports, the cess shall be imposed and collected on items so`
  line `imported and specified in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) The cess leviable under sub-section (1) on the items specified in the Schedule shall be in addition`
  line `to any cess or duty leviable on those items under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and the rules made thereunder and the`
  line `provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) and the rules made thereunder, as the case may be,`
  line `including those relating to refunds and exemptions from duties shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to`
  line `the levy and collection of cessleviable under this section and for this purpose, the provisions of the`
  line `Central Excise Act, 1944 and of the Customs Act, 1962, as the case may be, shall have effect as if the`
  line `aforesaid Acts provided for the levy of cess on all items specified in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `!. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for Heading (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for "Schedule" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206, for "not exceeding the rate set forth in the corresponding entry in column (3) of the`
  line `Schedule" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The first proviso omitted by s. 206, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 206, ibid, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (11365)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Crediting of cess to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11365&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of the cess levied under section`
  line `3 shall first be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India, and the Central Government may, if Parliament`
  line `by appropriation made by law in this behalf so provides, credit such proceeds to the Fund from time to`
  line `time, after deducting the expenses of collection, for being utilised exclusively for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (11366)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11366&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, credit by way of grants or loans such sums of`
  line `money as the Central Government may consider necessary in the Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (11367)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Establishment of Central Road and Infrastructure Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 206, ibid, for "Road Fund" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11367&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Establishment of Central ^1[Road and Infrastructure Fund].--(1) With effect from such date as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be`
  line `established for the purposes of this Act, a Fund to be called as the Central ^1[Road and Infrastructure`
  line Fund].
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be under the control of the Central Government and there shall be credited`
  line thereto--
  line
  line `(a) any sums of money paid under section 4 or section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) unspent part of the cess, being already levied for the purposes of the development and`
  line `maintenance of national highways;`
  line
  line `(c) the sums, if any, realised by the Central Government in carrying out its functions or in the`
  line `administration of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any fund provided by the Central Government for the development and maintenance of State`
  line roads.
  line
  line `(3) The balance to the credit of the Fund shall not lapse at the end of the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (11368)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Utilisation of the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11368&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Fund shall be utilised for the--`
  line
  line `(i) development and maintenance of national highways;`
  line
  line `(ii) development of the rural roads;`
  line
  line `(iii) development and maintenance of other State roads including roads of inter-State and`
  line `economic importance;`
  line
  line `^2[(iv) construction of roads either under or over the railways by means of bridges and erection of`
  line `safety works at unmanned rail-road crossings, new lines, conversion of existing standard lines into`
  line `gauge lines and electrification of rail lines; and`
  line
  line `(v) undertaking other infrastructure projects.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Act, the expression "infrastructure projects" means the`
  line `category of projects and infrastructure Sub-Sectors specified in Schedule II.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The Central Government may, depending upon the requirement for development of infrastructure`
  line `projects, and if it considers necessary or expedient to do so, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend`
  line `Schedule II relating to any Category of projects or Infrastructure Sub-Sectors.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be made,`
  line `the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 7 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for clauses (iv) and (v) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 206, ibid (w.e.f.1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (49379)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Apportionment of share of fund by Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 206, ibid (w.e.f.1-4-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=49379&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Apportionment of share of fund by Committee.--The share of the Fund to be apportioned to`
  line `each of infrastructure projects shall be finalised by a Committee, constituted by the Central Government`
  line `by notification published in the Official Gazette, headed by the Finance Minister, depending on the`
  line `priorities of the project.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (11369)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11369&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The concerned departments of the Central Government shall maintain`
  line `proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the`
  line `profit and loss account and the balance-sheet in respect of allocations of their shares of fund in such form,`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral`
  line `of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (11370)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers of Central Government to administer the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11370&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Powers of Central Government to administer the Fund.--^2[The Central Government`
  line `shall have the power to administer the Fund and shall--`
  line
  line `(a) take such decisions regarding investment on projects of roads and other infrastructure`
  line `as it considers necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) take such measures as may be necessary to raise funds for the development and`
  line `maintenance of roads and other infrastructure.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for heading "MANAGEMENT OF CENTRAL ROAD FUND" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 206, ibid, for section 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (11371)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions of the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11371&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Central Government shall be responsible for`
  line the--
  line
  line `(i) administration and management of the share of Fund allocated to the development and`
  line `maintenance of the ^2`
  line `[roads and other infrastructure];`
  line
  line `(ii) co-ordination and complete and timely utilisation of all sums allocated out of the Fund;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(iv) formulation of criteria on the basis of which the specific projects of State roads of inter-State`
  line `and economic importance are to be approved and financed out of share of State roads;`
  line
  line `^4[(v) release of funds to the States for specific projects and monitoring of such projects and`
  line `expenditure incurred thereon;`
  line
  line `(vi) formulation of the criteria for allocation of the funds for development and maintenance of`
  line `national highways and other infrastructure projects;]`
  line
  line `(vii) allocation of share of funds to each State and Union territory specified in the First Schedule to`
  line `the Constitution;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (viii) of sub-section (1), the Central Government`
  line `shall, with effect from the 1st day of March, 2005, allocate fifty paise from the amount of rupee two as`
  line `amended by sections 119 and 120 of the Finance Act, 2005 as the additional duty of customs and the`
  line `additional duty of excise on petrol, levied under sub-section (1) of section 103 and sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 111, as the case may be, of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1998 (21 of 1998) and the additional duty of`
  line `customs and the additional duty of excise on high speed diesel oil levied under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `116 and sub-section (1) of section 133, as the case may be, of the Finance Act, 1999 (27 of 1999),`
  line `exclusively for the development and maintenance of national highways.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 10 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by 18 of 2005, s. 121 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206, for "national highways" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (iii) omitted by s. 206, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 206, ibid., for clause (v) and (vi) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (viii) omitted by s. 206, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 121 (w. e. f. 13-5-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (11372)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Administration of States' share of the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018). .`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11372&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The share of the Fund to be spent on`
  line `development and maintenance of roads shall be allocated in such manner as may be decided by the`
  line `Committee referred to in section 7A].`
  line
  line `(2) The portion of the Fund allocated for expenditure in the various States and Union territories shall`
  line `be retained by the Central Government until it is actually required for expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) If in the opinion of the Central Government, the Government of any State or the administration of`
  line `any Union territory has at any time--`
  line
  line `(a) failed to take such steps as the Central Government may recommend for the regulation and`
  line `control of motor vehicles within the State or the Union territory; or`
  line
  line `(b) delayed without reasonable cause the application of any portion of the Fund allocated or reallocated, as the case may be, for expenditure within the State or Union territory,`
  line `the Central Government may resume the whole or part of any sums which it may have at that time held`
  line `for expenditure in that State or the Union territory.`
  line
  line `(4) All sums resumed by the Central Government from the account of any State Government or`
  line `Union territory administration as aforesaid shall be re-allocated between the credit accounts of the`
  line `defaulting and other State Governments and Union territory administrations in the ratio of the main`
  line `allocation for the financial year preceding the year in which the re-allocation is made.`
  line
  line `(5) The balance to the credit of the Fund in respect of any allocation shall not lapse at the end of the`
  line `financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (11373)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11373&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) specify ^1[the type of projects] in respect of which the funds may be disbursed under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the accounts shall be maintained and the annual statement of accounts`
  line `may be prepared including the profit and loss account and the balance-sheet under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the schemes for development and maintenance of State roads of interState`
  line `and economic importance are to be formulated and sanctioned under section 10 ^2***;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter for which rule is to be made, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206 for "the projects" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018)`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "under section 10" omitted by s. 206, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (11374)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Rules made under this Act to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11374&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (11375)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Provisions relating to existing Central Road and Infrastructure Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11375&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `14. Provisions relating to existing Central ^1[Road and Infrastructure Fund].--With effect from the appointed day the`
  line `Central Road Fund governed by the Parliamentary Resolution dated the 13th May, 1988 (hereafter`
  line `referred to in this section as the existing Fund) shall be deemed to be the Fund established under this Act`
  line and,--
  line
  line `(a) all schemes relating to development and maintenance of national ^2[highways, State roads and`
  line `other infrastructure] sanctioned under the existing Fund in so far as such schemes are relatable to the`
  line `schemes under this Act, shall be deemed to be the schemes sanctioned under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) all funds accrued under the existing Fund including assets and liabilities shall be transferred to`
  line `the Fund established under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 206, for "road Fund" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 206, ibid, for "highways and State roads" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (11376)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465&sectionId=11376&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00004_200054_1517807323465
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Road Fund Ordinance, 2000 (Ord. 5 of 2000) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
